ratings.comment: Her breathing is extremely annoying, the class requires too much studying for 3 credits, and she believes that her opinion is always the right one... creates some difficulties because she gets frustrated when people aren't participating, but the reason they don't is because she always shoots down your input.
I didn't think the class was bad at all; tricky, and lots of memorization, but you know exactly what to study and what you're responsible for.
You never know when she's going to have a beef with you. Moody, dramatic, and not easy going.

Prof. Murray isn't all bad. I think she has a few too many expectations of her new students background in Asian art. The class is easy to fall asleep in and still get decent grades on the tests. She is a little harsh in personality, sort of like an old, English nanny who hates children. All things considered, I'd take another class of hers.

the way she talks is really annoying, and i agree; probably the wicked witch of the west. if you take 203 make sure to take it with professor Quitman Phillips. he is very nice, but the class is hard no matter what

Holy****, this lady is the wicked witch of the west!!!  She can be totally harsh if you ask a "dumb" question in class, which means every question you COULD ask...and while she does give you flashcards for the exam, they are still nearly impossible!  Beware!  (Not work 3 credits)
